casebody.data:
No. 9744. MRS. PETER C. WILHELM, Claimant and Respondent, v. KELSEN LUMBER COMPANY and LIBERTY NATIONAL INSURANCE COMPANY, Appellants.

No. 9744.

310 Pac. (2d) 614. Decided May 13, 1957. Small & Herron, Helena, for appellant. Frame, Foley & Holland, Butte, for respondent. MR. CHIEF JUSTICE HARRISON:

Upon reading and filing the stipulation of the parties to the above entitled action, and the Court being fully advised in the premises;

It is hereby ordered and this does order, that the'above entitled appeal be, and the same is hereby dismissed with prejudice, each party to pay his, her or its own costs.
